{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-080","title":"买首饰","sectionId":"chapter-04","sectionTitle":"商店购物买买买","pageStart":411,"pageEnd":415,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":7,"duplicateEntryCount":25,"pages":[{"number":411,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"80 买首饰"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"necklace [ˈnekləs]","headword":"necklace"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.项链"}]},{"number":412,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"diamond earring钻石耳坠","headword":"diamond earring"},{"type":"entry","text":"pin [pɪn]","headword":"pin"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.胸针，饰针"},{"type":"note","text":"◎diamond pin钻石胸针"},{"type":"entry","text":"sweater chain 毛衣链","headword":"sweater chain"}]},{"number":413,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"jewel craft 宝石工艺","headword":"jewel craft"}]},{"number":414,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"jewellery box 首饰盒","headword":"jewellery box"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"text","text":"有趣的小词ring"},{"type":"text","text":"1. Let me ring that up for you!让我帮你结账吧！"},{"type":"text","text":"“结账”最标准的讲法是check out，例如你选好了东西，就可以拿"},{"type":"text","text":"到收银台，跟店员说I want to check out. 在美国，有些店员也喜欢用"},{"type":"entry","text":"ring it up这个习语，也是“结账”的意思。如果有机会去美国购物，你","headword":"ring it up"},{"type":"text","text":"看上了某件物品，就可以跟店员说Go ahead and ring it up for me. （帮"},{"type":"text","text":"我结账吧。）她肯定会惊讶于你会说这么地道的美语。"}]},{"number":415,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Does that ring a bell?有没有帮你想起一些什么啊？"},{"type":"text","text":"别人听不懂某个问题，你给出一点提示或解释后，就可以问他"},{"type":"text","text":"（她）Does that ring a bell? ring a bell的意思是“使人总算想了起来”。"},{"type":"text","text":"比如，你问一个人Do you know Jane?他（她）回答No, I don’t. 那你就"},{"type":"text","text":"可以继续说She is living with Mary, long hair and about 20 years old. Does"},{"type":"text","text":"that ring a bell?"}]}]}